The paper deals with a randomized point location structure for planar subdivisions of kinetic line segments, which is a topic in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses dynamization of the structure, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions expected time complexity, which is related to probability and statistics, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses adaptation for the online setting, which involves control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments and implementation, which are related to computer graphics, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible sub-category.
